@node CB_Author "ChoiceBar/Author"
@prev CB_Copyrights
@next CB_Credits


         @{b}Author@{ub}

   I'm a 24 years old student at University of Computer Science placed
   in Turin, Italy. I'm very interested about everything concerned with
   computers, expecially Amiga systems. 
   I started programming on Amiga some years ago when i purchased a copy
   of AMOS Professional. Some years later i decided to learn C because
   i had to use it at university. Now i know a lot of programming languages:
   C/C++,Pascal,Modula 2,a bit of 68K assembly,AMOS,BlitzBasic2,a bit of
   Prolog and SmallTalk, a bit of Java and so on...

   On @{b}Aminet@{ub} you can find some of my programs/utilities/mods:

   @{b}Bitmania@{ub}: silly name, isn't it? This is a simple program
         to convert numbers. Written using AMOS Pro (sigh... ).

   @{b}SCrypter@{ub}: simple crypter written in C
   
   @{b}ShowFont@{ub}: a font viewer for any Amigas (working on KS 1.3 too)
   
   @{b}ShapeGen@{ub}: V1.2 A simple program to generate BlitzBasic2 shapes
            using IFF brushes

   @{b}A Reason To love@{ub}: an Octamed module dedicated to my @{b}(ex)@{ub}friend Laura.

   @{b}SeaShell Demo@{ub}: SeaShell V1.1 demo, a front-end for Shelly.
  
   @{b}IdentifyBB2@{ub}: a Blitz Basic tutorial about Identify.library by
                              @{i}Richard Koerber@{ui}. Now at version 1.1.

   @{b}EssencED@{ub}: an utility to make usable under Imagine 2.9+ all textures
		provided with the Essence Collection (c).

   @{b}ChoiceBar@{ub}: V1.0 THIS utility....

   Now i'm working on several projects:

   @{b}SeaShell@{ub}: V1.2 a front-end for Shelly,a 3D seashells generator.
   @{b}ShockED@{ub}: An electric-circuits CAD program for the Amiga.
   @{b}Aphasia@{ub}: a shoot-em-up game for any Amiga.
